Adventures.LURU1-4 Prey for the Night:
{{Main|Prey for the Night}}
{{Quote|''The Eastern Glimmerwood is avoided by all but the most foolhardy with good reason. For here, in the lands of the People of the Black Blood, the civilized races are not the hunter; here they are nothing but prey. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in Luruar for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Bill W. Baldwin]]
* '''Released:''' April 2009
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

Adventures.LURU1-5 Beyond the Wild Frontier:
{{Main|Beyond the Wild Frontier}}
{{Quote|''The North is populated with many peoples, amongst them the savage and noble Uthgardt Barbarians. The balance of power is fragile in the wilderness; is it about to change? A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in Luruar for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Ian Hambly]]
* '''Released:''' August 2009
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

Adventures.LURU1-6 Desperate Times:
{{Main|Desperate Times}}
{{Quote|''Traveling the Nether Mountains has always been risky with bandits and shades looking for loot. Now it seems the undead are involved as more caravans go missing. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in Luruar for characters levels 4&ndash;7.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Ian Hayward]]
* '''Released:''' October 2009
* '''Levels:''' 4{{th}} &ndash; 7{{th}}

Adventures.LURU1-7 Demonic Dealings:
{{Main|Demonic Dealings}}
{{Quote|''Deep in the Glimmerwood the Uthgardt Barbarians keep the orcs of Luruar in check. A new ally to the orcs changes the balance of power. House Itharwen, unfortunate victims of the new alliance is seeking heroes to recover their losses in this battle. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in Luruar for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[David Birchall]]
* '''Released:''' December 2009
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

Adventures.LURU2-2 Shadows of the Knights:
{{Main|Shadows of the Knights}}
{{Quote|''The Uthgardt Barbarians are on the move, but not against their longtime enemy orcs. This time they are raiding frontier towns and merchant caravans. What has caused this new aggression? A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in Luruar for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Mickey Tan]]
* '''Released:''' June 2010
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

Adventures.LURU2-3 Forgotten Crypts, Hidden Dangers:
{{Main|Forgotten Crypts, Hidden Dangers}}
{{Quote|''A collapse in the famous Lady's College of Silverymoon reveals a network of forgotten catacombs. Engineers are sent down to ensure the stability of the university building, but more broods in the tunnels below than wood rot and crumbling walls. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in Luruar for character levels 1&ndash;4. First part of the "Forbidden Lore" series, ending in LURU2-4 (levels 4&ndash;7).''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Pierre van Rooden]]
* '''Released:''' August 2010
* '''Levels:''' 1{{st}} &ndash; 4{{th}}
